      "FacilityID": 1000100604,
      "SummaryText": "Executive Summary for the Erie County Water Authority Sturgeon Point and Van de Water-Water Treatment Plants.   \r\n\r\nAccident Release Prevention Policy: The Authority will take every reasonable action to prevent all accidental releases. This is accomplished by using the most current design, training, and inspecting processes available. The Authority's prevented maintenance program includes:\r\n\r\n1)      Analysis of the scrubber media tested once per year, verification the scrubber neutralization capacity for chlorine.\r\n2)\tScrubber equipment is tested weekly for proper operation.\r\n3)      The Halogen eclipse automatic shutoff valves are annually factory tested and certified. \r\n3)\tGas detectors/monitors are tested weekly. \r\n4)\tChlorine zinc plated flexible connectors replaced yearly.\r\n5)      Chlorine manifold piping and header valves are replaced every 5 years.\r\n6)      Chlorine automatic switchover preventative maintenance annually\r\n7)      Chlorine vacuum regulator preventative maintenance annually.\r\n8)      Chlorine chlorinator preventative maintenance annually.\r\n9)      Full face respiratory inspected and cleaned monthly.\r\n\r\n\r\nOperating and maintenance procedures are reviewed annually and are officially approved as the accepted operating procedures. \r\nPersonnel are annually trained on operation, maintenance and chlorine safety procedures. \r\nThe Stationary Source for Chlorine (CAS No. 7782-50-5) remains the same since the original RMP 1999.\r\n\r\nSturgeon Point Worst -Case Scenario\r\nThe Worst-case Scenario was reviewed and revised in March 2022, using EPA OCA Guidance Manual and Tables, with an affected zone radius of 1.3 miles for an urban topography, with obstructions, including: residential/suburbs housing, recreation areas, commercial/industrial areas all surrounded by a significant concentration of mature wooded areas.\r\n\r\nThe Alternative Release Scenario was reviewed and revised in March 2022, with an affected zone radius of 0.2 miles, for an urban topography, that"
    },
    {
      "ESSeqNum": 1,
      "FacilityID": 1000100604,
      "SummaryText": "only contains the plant site with obstructions, including: various buildings, with the site mainly surrounded by mature wooded areas.  \r\n\r\nSturgeon Point\r\nThe Fire Chief and volunteers of the Highland Hose Volunteer Fire Company, Evans NY and Erie County HAZMAT Team annually reviews and inspects the Sturgeon Point treatment plant.  The last onsite visit and coordination meeting was held on March 25, 2022.\r\n\r\nSturgeon Point Maintenance Updates:  Equipment maintenance completed as per above Maintenance Program.  No new updates, or changes to equipment since 2016 submission.\r\n \r\n\r\nTraining\r\nThe Authority continues to provide additional Hazwoper training as Hazmat Site Coordinators to assist the Emergency Service Hazmat team in the event of major chlorine release . \r\n\r\nEmployee Participation Annual Training, includes annual standard procedures and chlorine safety training, with opportunity to suggest changes."
    }
